  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Grate the <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on)</p><p>Trim and finely slice the <strong>spring onions</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1614004427040-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1614004427040-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1614004427040-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1614004427040-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1614004427040-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>grated potato </strong>to the middle of a tea towel and bring the four corners together to form a ball, then twist the ball and squeeze out as much liquid as you can</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614004442269-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614004442269-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614004442269-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614004442269-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1614004442269-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>potato</strong> <strong>mixture</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong>, <strong>smoked paprika </strong>and<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add<strong> </strong>1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and<strong> </strong>give everything a good mix up</p><p>Separate the mixture into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> and shape into firm potato cakes, approx 1cm thick</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1614004454585-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1614004454585-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1614004454585-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1614004454585-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1614004454585-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>potato cakes</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side until golden and crispy</p><p>Once done, add them to a plate and set aside (reserve the pan) – these are your <strong>potato röstis</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? You may need to do this in 2 batches!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1614004495212-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1614004495212-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1614004495212-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1614004495212-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1614004495212-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the röstis are cooking, add the <strong>smoked</strong> <strong>streaky bacon </strong>to one side of a baking tray (use<strong> tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!)</p><p>Add the <strong>asparagus spears</strong> to the other side of the tray with a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use two trays!</p><p>Put the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> in the oven for 10-15 min until the bacon is crispy and the asparagus has softened</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1614004506449-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1614004506449-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1614004506449-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1614004506449-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1614004506449-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Bring a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> to a very gentle boil over a medium heat (make sure the water is only slightly bubbling, otherwise it may break the yolks!)</p><p>Once gently boiling, add <strong>half </strong>of the <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> (save the rest for later!)</p><p>Crack the <strong>eggs</strong> into the water and cook for 3-4 min</p><p>Once done, gently transfer the <strong>poached eggs</strong> with a slotted spoon to kitchen paper and season them with <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
